Package org.severe.jripples.eig

EIG package, provides functionality for creating and manipulating JRipples EIG dependency graph.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
JRipplesEIGListener JRipplesEIGListener interface should be implemented by classes who wish to receive updates on lifecyle and content events of nodes and edges.
 

Class Summary
JRipplesEIG A software system can be viewed as a set of components and their interoperations and can be formally modeled as graph.
JRipplesEIGEdge JRipplesEIGEdge class represents a dependency (interoperation) between two nodes of the EIG (Evolving Interoperation Graph).
JRipplesEIGEdgeEvent JRipplesEIGEdgeEvent class represents lifecycle and content events that happen with a particular JRipplesEIGEdge.
JRipplesEIGEvent JRipplesEIGEvent represent an JRipplesEIG event that encapsulates various events of nodes and edges lifecyle, and content.
JRipplesEIGImportExport Converts JRipplesEIG state to an XML representation to be saved to disk,
and loads JRipplesEIG state from previously saved XML
JRipplesEIGNode JRipplesEIGNode class represents a node of the EIG (Evolving Interoperation Graph).
JRipplesEIGNodeEvent JRipplesEIGNodeEvent class represents lifecycle and content events that happen with a particular JRipplesEIGNode.
JRipplesIMemberServices A set of useful utilities for different evaluations of org.eclipse.jdt.core.IMember objects.
 

Package org.severe.jripples.eig Description

EIG package, provides functionality for creating and manipulating JRipples EIG dependency graph.
